Pre-Game Insights: India will be playing their last match of the ICC Men's ODI World Cup 2023 league stages against Netherlands at the M. Chinnaswamy Stadium in Bengaluru on November 12, Sunday.
The weather is likely to be mostly sunny and pleasant at the start of the game with minimal (2%) probability of precipitation.

Predicted Playing XI for India: Rohit Sharma (c), Shubman Gill, Virat Kohli, Shreyas Iyer, KL Rahul (wk), Suryakumar Yadav, Ravindra Jadeja, Ravichandran Ashwin, Shardul Thakur, Mohammed Shami, Mohammed Siraj.

Predicted Playing XI for Netherlands: Wesley Barresi, Max O'Dowd, Colin Ackermann, Sybrand Engelbrecht, Scott Edwards (c&wk), Teja Nidamanuru, Bas de Leede, Logan van Beek, Roelof van der Merwe, Aryan Dutt, Paul van Meekeren.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match will begin at 2 PM IST on November 12 and it will be telecast live on the Star Sports Network. It will also be streamed digitally simultaneously on Disney+Hotstar, with it being free to view for mobile users.
The climate will clear out by evening and the temperature will range around 19°C with no chances of rainfall or a shortened game on Sunday.
